comments.body: The minified release of `Clipboard` does not break for my local environment, but it does on staging. When I use a CDN for the source (e. g. `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/clipboard@2.0.6/dist/clipboard.js`) it works.

Adding `<script src="//cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/clipboard@2.0.6/dist/clipboard.js"></script>` to the `app/views/layouts/application.html.erb` view partial seems to be the only way I can find to resolve this. Explicitly importing from the source using `import ClipboardJS from '../../../node_modules/clipboard/dist/clipboard.js'` simply raises the same error (I suspect that this somehow relates to a Webpack configuration setting used to transpile the ES6 from the `clipboard` dependency).

`EventGenerator::OrangelightEventGenerator` test suites may also be failing intermittently (please see https://circleci.com/gh/pulibrary/figgy/25247#tests/containers/3) and `EventGenerator::GeoblacklightEventGenerator` (please see https://circleci.com/gh/pulibrary/figgy/25249#tests/containers/3)

I'm struggling to reproduce these failures by testing just these suites:

```bash
% bunx rspec --bisect spec/services/event_generator/geoblacklight_event_generator_spec.rb spec/services/event_generator/orangelight_event_generator_spec.rb
Bisect started using options: "spec/services/event_generator/geoblacklight_event_generator_spec.rb spec/services/event_generator/orangelight_event_generator_spec.rb"
Running suite to find failures...
Bisect failed!

No failures found. Bisect only works in the presence of one or more failing examples.
```

https://circleci.com/gh/pulibrary/figgy/25256?utm_campaign=vcs-integration-link&utm_medium=referral&utm_source=github-build-link passed without problems. I am still unable to reproduce these failures locally.
Now that the test suites are passing consistently, this should truly be ready for review and testing.
